<LXC version="0.1">
  <n>matrix</n>
  <Distribution>debian</Distribution>
  <Release>bookworm</Release>
  <Architecture>amd64</Architecture>
  <Repository>https://github.com/bmartino1/unraid-lxc-matrix</Repository>
  <Description>Matrix Synapse / Element Web / Jitsi Meet self-hosted stack</Description>
  <Privileged>true</Privileged>
  <Autostart>false</Autostart>
  <Beta>true</Beta>
  <Support>https://forums.unraid.net</Support>
  <Source>https://matrix.org/</Source>
  <Project>https://github.com/bmartino1/unraid-lxc-matrix</Project>
  <Overview>
    Full self-hosted secure communications stack on Debian 12 (Bookworm):
    Matrix Synapse homeserver, Element Web client, Jitsi Meet video (widget-only),
    Valkey cache, PostgreSQL 16, coturn TURN/STUN, and Nginx with SNI/TLS routing.

    After the LXC starts, open the console and run:
      cd /root
      ./setup.sh --domain chat.yourdomain.com

    All services should be pre-installed. setup.sh configures them for your domain. script folder to help manage
  </Overview>
  <Category>Tools: Network:</Category>
